      "message": "both BlitThreadOpCode and BlitThreadCmd are implementation details of the BlitThread class. I would recommend moving these under the private section of the latter class, as well as use an num class, e.g.:\n\n  class BlitThread : ... {\n  public:\n      ....\n  private:\n      enum class Opcode {\n          Init \u003d 0,\n          Blit \u003d 1,\n          Post \u003d 2,\n          SetWsCb \u003d 3,\n          Exit \u003d 4,\n      };\n\n      struct Cmd {\n          Opcode op \u003d Init;\n          FenceSync* sync \u003d nullptr;\n          HandleType windowSurface \u003d 0;\n          HandleType colorBuffer \u003d 0;\n      };\n\n      ...",
